      {
        "word": "consequence",
        "question": "Failure to follow the rules will have serious _______. ",
        "options": [
          "A. solutions",
          "B. consequences",
          "C. beginnings",
          "D. advantages"
        ],
        "answer": "B",
        "explanation": "\"consequences\" 意为后果，通常指不好的结果，符合句意中不遵守规则会带来严重的后果。"
      },
      {
        "word": "moreover",
        "question": "The hotel offers excellent service; _______, it's located in the city center.",
        "options": [
          "A. however",
          "B. therefore",
          "C. moreover",
          "D. despite"
        ],
        "answer": "C",
        "explanation": "\"moreover\" 意为此外、而且，用于添加额外信息或论据，符合句意中在提到服务好之后，补充说明地理位置优越。"
      },
      {
        "word": "attribute",
        "question": "Which of the following is NOT an _______ of a good leader?",
        "options": [
          "A. honesty",
          "B. responsibility",
          "C. laziness",
          "D. vision"
        ],
        "answer": "C",
        "explanation": "\"attribute\" 在此用作名词，意为属性或特征，而“懒惰”显然不是好领导的属性。"
      },
      {
        "word": "adapt",
